  <description type="morphology">Perennials; fibrous rooted, caudices woody, rhizomes absent. Stems not wandlike. Leaves deciduous or persistent, basal and/or cauline (petiolate or sessile, not in fascicles). Heads disciform. Receptacles epaleate, villous (hairs relatively long). Florets: peripheral 6–27 pistillate and fertile; central 15–100 bisexual and fertile; corollas (pale yellow) funnelform.</description>
  <description type="distribution">temperate regions, North America, South America, Eurasia.</description>
